arance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','three','','7.26'),(8730,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','four','','7.26'),(8731,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','five','','7.26'),(8732,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','six','','7.26'),(8733,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','inset','','7.26'),(8734,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Tablet landscape','','7.26'),(8735,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Tablet portrait','','7.26'),(8736,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Smalltouch landscape','','7.26'),(8737,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Global Settings','','7.26'),(8738,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Global Settings</h3><p>These settings are primarly set during development - do not change these unless you are actively developing or modifying your theme.</p>','','7.26'),(8739,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Mobile first or Mobile last','','7.26'),(8740,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Mobile first or Desktop first</h3>','','7.26'),(8741,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Change default layout method <small>(checking this will expose new settings)</small>','','7.26'),(8742,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<strong>Use with caution!</strong> If you are using a pre-styled sub-theme such as Pixture Reloaded, Sky, Corolla, AT Commerce or any of the commerical sub-themes you should NOT change this!','','7.26'),(8743,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Change default layout method','','7.26'),(8744,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<p>Adaptivetheme supports both mobile first and desktop first design approaches. Please review the <a href=\"!docs_link\" target=\"_blank\">online documentation</a>.</p><p>This setting fundementally alters what CSS is loaded and how it is loaded. At the most basic level if you select Mobile first the Smalltouch portrait layout will load as the default, if you select Desktop first the Standard layout will load as the default. Many other changes take place regarding loading of CSS for Internet Explorer, Responsive Gpanels and Panels as well.</p> ','','7.26'),(8745,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Mobile first','','7.26'),(8746,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Desktop first','','7.26'),(8747,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Disable Responsive Layout','','7.26'),(8748,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Disable Responsive Layout</h3>','','7.26'),(8749,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Disable responsive layout and styles','','7.26'),(8750,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','By checking this setting the site will use only the Standard layout and the global styles. You can turn this back on at any time.','','7.26'),(8751,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','File Management','','7.26'),(8752,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>File Management Settings</h3><p>Set the path to generated files and configure CSS and JS aggregation optimizations. Please read the help descriptions carefully. </p>','','7.26'),(8753,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Path to Generated Files','','7.26'),(8754,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Path to Generated Files</h3>','','7.26'),(8755,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','By default the generated files are saved in <a href=\"!file_settings_path\" target=\"_blank\">public files</a>. You can change this to your theme directory or a custom directory. These files include all the generated CSS files, the info file backup and color scheme backups if you are using the Color module. For more information see the docs on the <a href=\"!file_generation_system\" target=\"_blank\">file generation system</a>.','','7.26'),(8756,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Theme directory','','7.26'),(8757,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Custom path','','7.26'),(8758,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<div class=\"description\">Files will be saved to: <code>@public_files</code></div>','','7.26'),(8759,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<div class=\"description\">Files will be saved to: <code>@theme_directory</code></div>','','7.26'),(8760,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Enter the custom path:','','7.26'),(8761,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','This directory must exist and be writable by Drupal. This directory must be relative to the Drupal installation directory and be accessible over the web. Do not try to use something like <code>../css</code>, it will fail. Use someting like <code>sites/default/css</code>.','','7.26'),(8762,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','CSS aggregation is OFF. This settings will have no effect until CSS aggregation is turned ON.','','7.26'),(8763,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','JavaScript aggregation is OFF. This settings will have no effect until JavaScript aggregation is turned ON.','','7.26'),(8764,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Combine Aggregated Files','','7.26'),(8765,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Combine Aggregated Files <sup>(beta)</sup></h3><p>When CSS aggregation is on Drupal aggregates CSS and JS files by group. These settings will override this and create one CSS stylesheet per type and only one JavaScript file. This reduces HTTP requests and improves site performance. Note: this is beta and while well tested you should check your site carefully, both the style and behavior.</p><p>Warning: Internet Explorer cannot handle more than 4095 selectors in one stylesheet - combining CSS files using this setting could result in more than 4095 selectors. If you see probems such as no style in IE then turn this off.</p>','','7.26'),(8766,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Combine CSS Files','','7.26'),(8767,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<p>In AT you will normally get three media type CSS files after this is enabled and CSS aggregation is turned on - all, screen and only screen. If you are using a print stylesheet this will be seperate also. Browser specific stylesheets for Internet Explorer are ignored.</p><p>!css_mode_message</p>','','7.26'),(8768,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Combine JS Files','','7.26'),(8769,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<p>This will force all aggregated JavaScript files into one file.</p><p>!js_mode_message</p>','','7.26'),(8770,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','CSS','','7.26'),(8771,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>CSS Settings</h3><p>Here you can get feedback on what mode your site is currently using, and enable the optional <code>responsive.custom.css</code> file.</p>','','7.26'),(8772,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<p><strong><a href=\"!settings_path\" target=\"_blank\">CSS aggregation</a> is OFF</strong>. Changes to your themes responsive CSS files will show automatically.</p><p><div class=\"description\"><p>Note: when CSS aggregation is ON you need to re-save the theme settings if you make any changes to your themes responsive stylesheets. This is required to re-write the production version of the responsive styles and is a performance optimization in Adaptivetheme, which saves your site at least 4 HTTP requests.</p></div>','','7.26'),(8773,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','CSS Mode','','7.26'),(8774,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Mode</h3>','','7.26'),(8775,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Custom Media Queries','','7.26'),(8776,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Custom Media Queries</h3>','','7.26'),(8777,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Enable the responsive.custom.css file','','7.26'),(8778,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<p>Use this file if you need to use custom media queries, such as <a href=\"!zomigi\" target=\"_blank\">overlapped media queries</a>.</p><p><strong>File location:</strong> <code>@theme_path/css/responsive.custom.css</code>, .scss version: <code>@theme_path/sass/responsive.custom.scss</code></p>','','7.26'),(8779,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Polyfills','','7.26'),(8780,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Polyfills</h3><p>Here you can enable commonly used Polyfills supplied with the core theme. Adaptivetheme also supports loading <a href=\"!docspage\" target=\"_blank\">scripts and CSS for Internet Explorer</a> using your sub-themes info file.','','7.26'),(8781,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','HTML5 support in IE','','7.26'),(8782,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','By checking this setting the site will load the <a href=\"!html5shiv_link\" target=\"_blank\">html5shiv</a>. Turning this off will be bad news for IE6-8.','','7.26'),(8783,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','matchMedia.js Polyfill','','7.26'),(8784,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Backport matchMedia support to unsupporting browsers - see <a href=\"!matchmedia_link\" target=\"_blank\">github.com/paulirish/matchMedia</a>. If using the Menu Toggle extension you need this if supporting Android 2.3 or earlier is important. Do not enable this if you are using respond.js (see <em>Media query support for IE6-8</em>, below) or Modernizr. A number of other libraries load this polyfill also - it\'s worth checking, although its also a very small polyfill.','','7.26'),(8785,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Responsive JavaScript <sup>(deprecated)</sup>','','7.26'),(8786,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','This is deprecated because AT Core now loads it\'s media queries into Drupals JS settings - see <code>menu-toggle.js</code> in the core theme for an example of how this can be used with matchMedia. This legacy feature loads the <a href=\"!onmediaquery_link\" target=\"_blank\">JS Media Queries</a> plugin to enable responsive JavaScript. See <code>@script_filepath</code> for instructions on how to use. This is an alternative to using matchMedia.','','7.26'),(8787,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Fix CSS rounding errors in IE6-7','','7.26'),(8788,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Load a stylesheet that fixes percentage rounding errors in IE6-7. You need this if you are using Gpanels or Panels layouts.','','7.26'),(8789,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Media query support for IE6-8 (respond.js)','','7.26'),(8790,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','By checking this setting IE6, 7 and 8 will rely on <a href=\"!respondjs_link\" target=\"_blank\">respond.js</a> to set the layout.','','7.26'),(8791,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Scalefix for iOS','','7.26'),(8792,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Fixes the iOS Orientationchange zoom bug. See <a href=\"!scalefix_link\" target=\"_blank\">github.com/scottjehl/iOS-Orientationchange-Fix</a>.','','7.26'),(8793,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','Metatags','','7.26'),(8794,'/fr/admin/appearance/settings/mondrupal_front','default','<h3>Mobile Metatags</h3><p>Configure meta